A firefighter fell from the upper floors of a government building in the Johannesburg CBD while battling a blaze there on Wednesday morning. Johannesburg Emergency Services spokesperson Nana Radebe told News24 that paramedics were on scene. Tweets from Independent Online confirmed that a body lay on the pavement next to the building. Radebe said the building was evacuated after the fire broke. Further details were not immediately available. While we have your attention... An increasingly rare commodity, quality independent journalism costs money - though not nearly as much as its absence. Every article, every day, is our contribution to  Defending Truth in South Africa.
